data.description: Simply charming  4 BR / 2.5 Bath Dutch Colonial home nestled on a  cul-de-sac in the heart of Alexandria's Belle Haven community.   Features include hardwood floors, newer windows (2020), and neutral paint throughout.  The main level is perfect for entertaining with comfortable rooms that are ideal for entertaining!  Cozy up in the living room by the wood-burning fireplace or enjoy a morning coffee in the breakfast nook. The eat-in kitchen features a bar, white cabinets, quartz countertops (2015), and stainless steel appliances,  Just off of the kitchen, easily access the expansive deck (Trex product 2020) that overlooks mature trees and is the perfect place for barbeques and entertaining.   Upstairs the hardwood floors continue. and there are four nice-sized bedrooms with ample closet space. Including a primary suite that includes a  luxurious spa bathroom (2021).   Located on the lower level of the home, the family room is the perfect spot for movie nights and has an adjacent half bath and walk-out access to a lower-level patio space. Laundry room washer & dryer were updated (2021).  The unfinished basement includes tons of storage and includes a workshop bench, refrigerator, and access to the HVAC  & water heater (both updated in 2020).   The roof was replaced (2021) and a solar panel energy system was installed  (2021).   Enjoy significantly reduced electric costs while reducing your carbon footprint! Welcome home to Belle Haven!  Close to GW Pkwy, Old Town. Just 5 miles south of National Landing.
